{"comments":null,"declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Generate an icosahedron (20-faced regular polyhedron).\n\nThe icosahedron is defined by 12 vertices and 20 triangular faces.\nDetail level controls subdivision: 0 = 20 triangles, n = 20 × 4^n triangles.\n\nGolden ratio: φ = (1 + √5) / 2 ≈ 1.618\nVertices lie at (0, ±1, ±φ) and cyclic permutations.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","GPU","Scene3D","Mesh"],"IcosahedronMeshParams"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","GPU","WebGPU","Scene3D","Geometry","Core"],"MeshData"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[50,57],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/GPU/WebGPU/Scene3D/Geometry/Platonic.purs","start":[50,1]},"title":"generateIcosahedron"},{"children":[],"comments":"Generate an octahedron (8-faced regular polyhedron).\n\nThe octahedron has 6 vertices at (±1, 0, 0), (0, ±1, 0), (0, 0, ±1)\nand 8 triangular faces.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","GPU","Scene3D","Mesh"],"OctahedronMeshParams"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","GPU","WebGPU","Scene3D","Geometry","Core"],"MeshData"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[102,55],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/GPU/WebGPU/Scene3D/Geometry/Platonic.purs","start":[102,1]},"title":"generateOctahedron"},{"children":[],"comments":"Generate a tetrahedron (4-faced regular polyhedron).\n\nThe simplest Platonic solid with 4 vertices and 4 triangular faces.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":